<font size="5">American Sign Language: "add"</font><br/>
<blockquote>
<hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
	The concept of "add" can be done a couple of ways.  
  <br/>
	Generally we either use the "plus" sign or the "add to" sign.<font face="Arial"><hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
</font>
<p><br/>
	ADD-to = "add" = "additionally" = "in addition to" 
	= "extra"<br/>
